Super Eagles coach Austin Eguaevon has restored defender Kenneth Omeruo and striker Taiwo Awoniyi to the starting lineup of the Round of 16 tie with Tunisia at the ongoing AFCON 2021 in Garoua, Cameroon. Also back are midfielder Ayo Aribo and Samuel Chukwueze, who were dropped for the last group game against Guinea-Bissau.   Buni orders investigation as armed men shoot driver dead in…     La Liga: Real Madrid, Elche settle for draw     EPL: Chelsea beat Tottenham Hotspur 2 – 0   XI: Omeruo, W. Troost-Ekong, Aina, M. Simon, Ndidi, Iheanacho, T. Awoniyi, J. Ayodele-Aribo, S. Chukwueze, Z. Sanusi, M. Okoye